						<summary>

						<p>Stone near the ruins of the Rāmappa temple.</p>						

						<p>Jagadēkamalla II (Undated).</p>						

						<p>This damaged inscription refers itself to the reign of Jagadēkamalla. It seems to register a gift made by <hi rend="italic">Suṅkaverggaḍes</hi> Ajja • • • • • karasarāja and Dēvaparāja to god Rāmēsvara.</p>						

						<p>In characters of 12th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
